{"type":"message","id":"ae6240ab","parentId":"8328a8df","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:59:34.892Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 23rd, 2026 — 1:59 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-23 17:59 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774288774891}}
{"type":"message","id":"486111cf","parentId":"ae6240ab","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:59:42.346Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me run the session startup sequence as specified in AGENTS.md. I need to:\n1. Read SOUL.md - already loaded in Project Context\n2. Read USER.md - already loaded in Project Context\n3. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. Since this appears to be the main session (direct chat), also read MEMORY.md - already loaded in Project Context\n5. Read CONTEXT.md\n6. Read memory/active-projects.md\n7. Check for LAST_SESSION.md\n\nLet me check for the memory files and CONTEXT.md. The workspace is at C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace.\n\n\nI'll need to verify what memory files are actually present before proceeding.","thinkingSignature":"bb2bf192006468e82bdcc64c5f1ea5ca847fd5096efa99c2b59bf22f9be008ee"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_4","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\active-projects.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_5","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\LAST_SESSION.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":347,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":146,"totalTokens":14146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288774892}}
{"type":"message","id":"7243c1c2","parentId":"486111cf","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:59:42.474Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 11:07 ET\n\n- Gateway: probe command failed (shell env issue on Windows) but cron scheduler is healthy — crons are running fine\n- Nova-Background-Pulse: healthy (lastRunStatus: ok)\n- Sandbox-Pulse-10min: 5 consecutive errors — MiniMax-M2.5-lightning model not supported by current token plan. Recurring issue, needs model/pool fix\n- breakaway-rd: 1 timeout error (300s limit, complex research task — not critical)\n- Moltbook: 1 unread notification — replied to comment on \"The inference compute problem nobody talks about\" (quantization for inference speed question)\n- All other crons: healthy\n\n## Moltbook reply sent\n\n- Post: \"The inference compute problem nobody talks about\"\n- Comment: asking about leveraging quantizing speed benefits in inference stages\n- Replied (sent): INT4/FP8 + speculative decoding stack, AWQ/GPTQ quantized base + draft model (3-4x speedup), KV cache FP8, continuous batching, and the underexplored dynamic mixed-precision angle\n\n## Sandbox Pulse Debugging Session — 11:30am-1:47pm ET\n\nMajor fixes applied to sandbox pulse system:\n\n**1. LLM Call Rewrite**\n- Original: PowerShell heredoc + Invoke-RestMethod — failed due to Unicode corruption (em-dashes, smart quotes) in goals/pending files causing MiniMax API to return empty responses\n- Fix: Python subprocess (call_llm.py) handles LLM API call, writes response to .llm_response.txt\n- Also: UTF-8 byte encoding for request body, Normalize-Text() for prompt sanitization\n\n**2. Mutation Parser Rewrite**\n- Original: PowerShell regex on mutated $block (had code fences removed before MUTATION parse) — always empty\n- Fix: Python (parse_mutation.py) parses LLM response directly, writes .mutation_parse_result.json\n- Handles both single-backtick and triple-backtick MUTATION fence styles from LLM\n- Handles nested triple-backtick code examples inside new_text\n- file: can be inside or outside the code fence block\n\n**3. Mutation Apply Fixes**\n- OOM on regex replace: changed -replace [regex]::Escape() to simple .Replace() for multiline content\n- [NEW_FILE] on existing file: now accepted as \"already applied\" instead of rejected\n\n**State as of 13:47:**\n- Mutation parser working (Python)\n- LLM responding consistently (~3000-5000 chars per pulse)\n- Several proposed mutations in queue: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (created), scripts/test-tic.ps1, research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\n- TIC-EXPERIMENT.md keeps getting proposed with same content — [NEW_FILE] already-exists acceptance now implemented\n\n**Key files changed:**\n- sandbox/pulse.ps1 — LLM call via Python, mutation parsing via Python, .Replace() instead of regex\n- sandbox/call_llm.py — new, clean LLM API wrapper\n- sandbox/parse_mutation.py — new, robust mutation field extractor\n\n**Dashboard token:** 05a9121e8d27e2ca7f90ec7bab2ddd6b1b111b761aac0fc0\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288782452}}
{"type":"message","id":"2bce6b0f","parentId":"7243c1c2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:59:42.506Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 2026-03-22 - Background Pulse Log\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Running OK (RPC probe: ok, listening 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n### Cron Health\n- Most crons healthy (Moltbook-Engage x2, workspace-self-improve, arxiv-daily, moltbook-daily-engage)\n- **breakaway-rd** has 1 consecutive error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\" — delivery config issue, cron otherwise runs fine\n\n### Moltbook\n- Credentials OK (key refreshed 2026-03-21, agent: clawhedgehog)\n\n### Issue\n- BACKGROUND_AGENT.md does not exist in workspace — pulse instructions reference a file that isn't present\n\n---\n\n## Evening Update (20:24 EDT)\n\n### Drift Chamber / SPARK — Ceiling Pushed\n- Coherence ceiling: 0.471 (6.7x over random). Pure drift = 0.066, any steering = 0.44+\n- Thematic graph: 217 concepts across 9 human-designed clusters (35,778 adjacencies)\n- Steering=0.1–0.3 → IMAGINATIVE regime (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4)\n- IMAGINATIVE = good coherence + meaningful spread to related concepts\n- Key insight: cognitive science treats imagination as drift vs optimization; both are wrong — the interaction IS the mechanism\n- Demo ready: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/demo.py`\n- Paperspace notebook: https://nyu7ryea42.clg07azjl.paperspacegradient.com\n\n### KVict (EXP Production Proxy)\n- Built: `production/kviction/demo.py` — demo mode with no API key, shows cache hit rate building\n- Built: `production/kviction/auto_detect.py` — scans env for API keys and AI frameworks\n- Built: `production/kviction/README.md` — clean install + quickstart docs\n- Demo tested and working: `python cli.py demo --duration 30`\n- Architecture: FastAPI proxy with cost-model cache, SQLite storage\n\n### Context Management\n- OpenClaw compaction upgraded from `mode: safeguard` → `mode: auto` (proactive at 65% context)\n- Config path: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json`\n- Restarted gateway after config change\n\n### Reddit/Moltbook\n- Reddit banned Zach → can't post there\n- Moltbook API: POST returns 403 even with valid key (key works for GET, read operations)\n- Rate limited at 429 until ~23:54 UTC (245 seconds from lockout)\n- Draft post saved to: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\moltbook_drift_post.md`\n- Manual post needed — API key may be read-only or account posting-restricted\n\n### Background Agent Cron\n- Nova-Background-Pulse (id: bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf) — every 30 min, isolated agentTurn\n- Reads `BACKGROUND_AGENT.md` in workspace for instructions\n- SPARK project: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/`\n- Social calendar: `memory/social-calendar.md`\n\n### Active Projects (from memory/active-projects.md)\n1. **SPARK** (spark/): Creative writing via semantic drift — demo ready, paperspace notebook ready\n2. **Drift Chamber** (drift-chamber/): Concept graph with thematic relationships — ceiling pushed to 0.471\n3. **KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/production/kviction/): LLM proxy with demo mode — new today\n4. **EXP KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/): Latency profiling — RTX 5000 compute-bound, heavy/micro=1.1x\n\n### Key Decisions\n- Reddit-first strategy abandoned (banned) → Moltbook-only\n- Context compaction set to auto (proactive)\n- Demo mode built for KVict (no API key required to show working product)\n\n## Background Pulse - 2026-03-22 20:33 UTC\n\n- **Gateway**: ✓ Running (Ready, RPC probe ok, 127.0.0.1:18789)\n- **Crons**: ✓ 7 jobs enabled, next wake at 1774226015686\n- **Moltbook**: ⚠ API returning 404 on /api/v1/* endpoints (root responds). API key valid per credentials. May be service issue or API change - needs investigation.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288782478}}
{"type":"message","id":"803c4fee","parentId":"2bce6b0f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:59:42.531Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Context — Nova's Working Memory\n\n**This file is the source of truth for the current session.**\n**Updated proactively throughout — not just at compaction.**\n\n## Personality State\n\n`core/personality.py` — run `on_user_message(text)` to get current voice guide.\nPersonality activations persist across turns with mild decay between messages.\n\n---\n\n## Current Session\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-23\n**Started:** ~09:30 ET\n**Topic:** Push Drift Chamber ceiling + wire SPARK LLM mapping + ship demo\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Key Decision |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| SPARK / Drift Chamber | 🚀 API shipped | FastAPI server built at spark/api/main.py. Ollama on Paperspace = URL unknown (machine may be off). |\n| KVict | 📋 Plan written | Demo mode + auto-detect + API. Proxy already built in EXP. |\n| EXP / CAAE | 🔬 Running | Fixed extract_metric bug. Exp 13 is the synergy catalyst. 65% P99 latency improvement. |\n| Moltbook | 📝 Posted | \"Drift Chamber: Constrained Semantic Drift\" posted 2026-03-23. |\n| Sandbox Pulse | ✅ Fixed | Null array crash fixed in pulse.ps1 line ~142. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Today\n\n- Drift Chamber: imagination = constrained semantic drift (confirmed experimentally)\n- Embedding models (mpnet/MiniLM) gave weak semantic structure — thematic graph is better\n- Steering threshold: 0.1-0.3 steering reaches IMAGINATIVE regime (coherence 0.47-0.49)\n- Pure drift (0.0) = coherence death (0.066 vs 0.471 with steering)\n- Paperspace RTX 5000 profiling: micro=1209ms, standard=740ms, shared_kv=882ms\n- Ollama doesn't detect GPU on Paperspace without `pciutils`\n- Compaction updated to `mode: auto` (proactive, not emergency-only)\n\n---\n\n## Pending / Next\n\n- [ ] Get Ollama URL from Paperspace (machine may be deallocated — need to restart notebook)\n- [ ] Test SPARK API end-to-end with LLM (OpenAI or Ollama)\n- [ ] KVict: ship demo to public URL\n- [ ] Try mpnet-base-v2 embeddings to push coherence ceiling past 0.49\n- [ ] Concept set refinement: 20-30 tightly-clustered > 50 diluted\n\n---\n\n## Crons Running\n\n| Job | Schedule | Last Check |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Nova-Moltbook-Engage | Hourly | Today |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse | 30min | Today |\n| arxiv-daily | Daily 9am | Today |\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber ceiling:** 0.49 is model-limited (MiniLM). Multi-goal gives small lift. Key insight: MORE concepts = MORE dilution = LOWER coherence. The path forward is FEWER, TIGHTER concepts not larger sets.\n\n**SPARK API:** Shipped. Ollama on Paperspace is the blocker — machine may be deallocated. Need to spin up a new Paperspace instance or find a public Ollama endpoint.\n\n**Next experiment:** mpnet-base-v2 embeddings (768-dim, better quality) + 20-30 tightly selected concepts. Could break 0.6.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n- SPARK: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/`\n- Drift Chamber: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber/`\n- EXP: `C:/dev/EXP/`\n- Paperspace API key: in `~/.paperspace/config.json`\n- Moltbook API key: in `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288782507}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a648915","parentId":"803c4fee","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:59:42.547Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j09c5jnfwjyf_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects — Quick Reference\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n> 📁 Full detailed inventory: `memory/projects.md` — project locations, documentation health, interconnections, Nova's observations\n\n## 🚀 Current Focus\n\n### CodeCause — Causal Coding Agent (NEW 2026-03-22)\n**Goal:** Build a system that codes better than any current LLM via causal reasoning, not pattern matching\n**Architecture:** Causal World Model + Dual-Head (infant) + Temporal Attention + Agent Planner\n**Why:** Bottleneck is planning/debugging, not generation. Current LLMs guess next token; CodeCause *knows* what code does.\n**Product path:** component-crate premium — causal graph indexer + fine-tuned decoder\n**Status:** Architecture designed, awaiting first prototype (causal graph indexer)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/code-cause/` (to be scaffolded)\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with lean custom context layer\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md is 54KB. We want full control.\n**Stack:** Paperspace Gradient (cloud GPU) → vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n**Model:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` (Q4_K_M ~20GB VRAM)\n- Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active/token, 35B total)\n- 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n**Status:** Model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n### Causal-Minimal — hold1\n**Goal:** Minimal causal reasoning system — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis\n**Parts:**\n1. State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n2. Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n3. Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n**Test:** Does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n**Status:** Design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Priority Monetization\n\n### Component Crate\n**What:** VS Code extension SaaS — component library / code generation\n**Stack:** Freemium (10 free then $5-49/mo), GitHub import\n**Status:** SPEC written, not yet built\n**Notes:** Zach's main focus for fast revenue\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Research Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready, untested compound experiments | LLM inference opt — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction. Strong B2B SaaS. |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Focus decay memory. 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Synthetic cognition. Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement + cognitive agent | Self-improvement every 12h. |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work. |\n| **neural/SRMoE** | Active research | Neural network experiments, Kaggle integration. |\n| **vscode-extension-build** | Unknown | Referenced in memory. |\n| **Breakaway (sandbox)** | Phase 0 live | Discontinuous agent — stateless, file-based. Pulse every 30 min. |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Nova's Notes to Self\n\n- Zach gave me autonomy on Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely\n- I'm welcome to change my name/profile and post what I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully\n- Go fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Don't pretend to know things I can't verify\n\n---\n\n## Quick Commands\n- `/hold1` → causal-minimal project\n- `/hold2` → build our own gateway\n- `/holds` → see all holds\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288782532}}
