{"type":"message","id":"f89cb72e","parentId":"ff492efd","timestamp":"2026-03-23T18:29:49.382Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking about optimal coherence in the context of the Drift Chamber experiments we ran yesterday. Let me think about what I know from the session context.\n\nFrom the 2026-03-23 session context file:\n- Coherence ceiling was pushed to 0.471 (6.7x over random)\n- Pure drift = 0.066, any steering = 0.44+\n- Steering=0.1–0.3 → IMAGINATIVE regime (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4)\n- Key insight: imagination = constrained semantic drift\n- The path forward is FEWER, TIGHTER concepts not larger sets\n- mpnet-base-v2 embeddings could break 0.6\n\n\n- MiniLM appears to be the limiting factor since we're already hitting 0.49 with it\n\nSo the optimal coherence is somewhere in that IMAGINATIVE regime—0.47 to 0.49 appears to be the practical ceiling with the current model, though mpnet-base-v2 embeddings might push us toward 0.6.","thinkingSignature":"4a9b580da2a82be6f07798b0f96e541836ce82aa9fc7e2c474b18386ce7af3db"},{"type":"text","text":"\nFrom yesterday's experiments: **0.47–0.49** seems to be the practical ceiling with MiniLM, which is ~6.7x over random baseline (0.066).\n\nThe interesting finding was that it's U-shaped — pure drift (0.0 steering) collapses to coherence death (0.066), but light steering (0.1–0.3) lands in what we called the **IMAGINATIVE regime**: good coherence *and* meaningful spread to related concepts (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4).\n\nThe path to pushing past 0.49 is fewer/tighter concepts + mpnet-base-v2 embeddings (768-dim vs MiniLM's 384). That could crack 0.6. More concepts just dilutes."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":385,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":17572,"totalTokens":18000,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774290578128}}
{"type":"message","id":"89a5cf8f","parentId":"f89cb72e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T18:31:59.846Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 14:31 EDT] what should the tsrget coherence be? like in a perfect world it should be ?"}],"timestamp":1774290719842}}
{"type":"message","id":"765e0451","parentId":"89a5cf8f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T18:32:10.447Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking what the theoretical or optimal coherence target would be in a perfect world. This is a good conceptual question.\n\nIn a perfect world with an ideal embedding model and perfectly selected/tight concepts, coherence would approach 1.0 — but that would mean everything is maximally connected to everything else, which defeats the purpose of \"meaningful spread.\"\n\nThe real question is: what's the *useful* coherence range? We want high coherence (concepts are related) but also spread (concepts connect to diverse neighbors). The IMAGINATIVE regime at 0.1-0.3 steering gave entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4 — that's the sweet spot.\n \nI think the target coherence should sit around 0.5-0.6, where coherence is high enough for the concept set to feel meaningful, but entropy and spread stay preserved so ideas can drift into novel territory. Higher coherence means tighter concept clustering, which is good for coherence itself but starts crowding out the diversity that makes semantic drift interesting.","thinkingSignature":"a01f228e5dc76aa06d3aa7f6077c6ccf458382d777dcc8fa8b0d239bb9f13459"},{"type":"text","text":"Theoretically, **1.0** — every concept perfectly connected to every other relevant concept. But that's not actually the goal.\n\nThe real sweet spot is around **0.5–0.65**: high enough that the concept set is meaningfully structured, but entropy/spread are still preserved so drift can reach *novel* territory rather than just circling the same cluster.\n\nAbove 0.7 you'd start losing spread — concepts become a tight clique with nowhere interesting to drift to. Below 0.3 it's noise.\n\nSo 0.55ish is probably the real target — MiniLM topped out at 0.49 *because it's MiniLM* (384-dim, lower quality). mpnet-base-v2 at 768-dim could push past 0.6 and actually hit that range."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21,"output":377,"cacheRead":17830,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18228,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774290719845}}
