{"type":"message","id":"b6585cc6","parentId":"560d4a4e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:09:02.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a persistent ClawHub platform bug. The error is in their Convex backend - `syncSkillSearchDigestsForOwnerPublisherId` runs multiple paginated queries when creating a new publisher, which violates Convex's single paginated query limit. \n\nThis is a bug on the ClawHub side, not something I can fix. I should let Zach know the skill is polished and ready, but there's a platform bug preventing publish. Maybe I can try checking the ClawHub website/API directly to see if there's another way.\n\nActually, let me check if this is a known issue by looking at the clawhub CLI source or check if there's a way to publish via API directly.","thinkingSignature":"566bf8e0784c56e52319f91212f376175acd77e2d2157ff48254ea2334f8e367"},{"type":"text","text":"ClawHub has a backend bug — their Convex function runs multiple paginated queries when setting up a new publisher, which violates their own limit. It's on their side, not your code.\n\n**The skill is polished and ready.** What I fixed:\n- Created missing `references/nova.json` preset file\n- Removed nonexistent traits from `presets.md` (`philosophical`, `emotional`, `personal`, `impatient` → traits that weren't in the handler)\n- Cleaned up duplicate metadata in `hook.json`\n\nThe publish fails at the publisher-setup step before anything even gets uploaded. You could report this to the ClawHub maintainers — or try again later in case it's transient. It might also work if you log in via the web UI and publish from there."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22761,"output":303,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36674,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774292936115}}
