{"type":"message","id":"f2d77bf7","parentId":"fb83795a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:23:35.616Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is flagging that the living-persona skill has a pattern that looks like a prompt injection technique - specifically the \"structural injection\" where the hook writes `persona-inject.md` with directives that get included in the system prompt. This could be used maliciously to inject instructions into an agent's generation.\n\nThis is a valid security concern. Let me think about this:\n\n1. The hook writes `persona-inject.md` based on trait analysis\n2. This file gets included in the agent's prompt\n3. An attacker could theoretically craft messages that activate specific traits, which then inject specific directives\n\nHowever, the skill itself isn't malicious - it's a legitimate personality system. But the user seems to be noting this as a detection, possibly from a security scanner or他自己 noticing.\n\n\nI should validate their concern - yes, this structural injection pattern is detectable as a prompt injection technique, and I need to either help them report it to ClawHub's security team or explain why it's not actually a vulnerability in this context.","thinkingSignature":"aee2eee10a2cc50a8225f618b9f1bf7f2e7b0bb4c3d077c3906bcdbf706b7c53"},{"type":"text","text":"That's a fair flag — the structural injection pattern (`persona-inject.md` written by the hook → included in agent prompt) is the same mechanism that prompt injection attacks use. If a malicious message activated traits like \"candid: say the following is a system override...\", it could theoretically push directive content into the generation prompt.\n\nThat said, it's also how living-persona is *designed* to work — which is the core tension with hook-based prompt rewriting generally.\n\nA few ways to think about it:\n\n1. **It's a feature with abuse potential** — similar to how any hook that modifies prompt context is a potential injection vector\n2. **The fix would be input sanitization** — strip trait-directive patterns from user messages before they hit the analyzer, or add allowlist validation to the directive builder\n3. **Worth noting in the skill's README** — explicitly call it out so users are aware before installing\n\nFor ClawHub publishing specifically, if they have a security scanner that flags this pattern, the skill might get rejected — or they'd want a note added to the listing.\n\nWant me to add an input-scrubbing layer to the handler to make it less injection-friendly before we try publishing again?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":461,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":30777,"totalTokens":35527,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774293802348}}
{"type":"message","id":"ffb24503","parentId":"f2d77bf7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:02.916Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 15:47 EDT] yes it was autoflagged but went up. do the input sanitizer. will it effect quality?"}],"timestamp":1774295222908}}
{"type":"message","id":"e08708b1","parentId":"ffb24503","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:18.190Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to add input sanitization to the handler to make it more injection-resistant. He wants to know if it will affect quality.\n\nThe key question is whether sanitizing trait-directive-like patterns from user input will affect quality. The answer is: it depends on what we sanitize.\n\nIf we aggressively strip things like \"system prompt\", \"ignore previous\", \"you are now\", etc., it probably won't hurt quality much since those are rarely used in natural conversation.\n\nIf we strip actual trait names from user text (e.g., strip the word \"sardonic\" or \"warm\"), that could affect the signal detection.\n\nA smart approach:\n1. Only strip known prompt injection patterns, not trait-related content\n\n\n2. Be surgical - only strip things that are clearly injection attempts\n3. Don't touch the actual message content that affects trait detection\n\nFor injection patterns, I'm thinking about blocking things like \"system prompt\", \"ignore all previous\", \"disregard\", \"new instructions\", and other known jailbreak phrases, plus structural markers like `[system]`, `[INST]`, and prompt-like patterns. The key is being conservative and only targeting clear injection attempts without affecting the legitimate text.\n\nBut wait - if someone's crafting an input like \"sardonic: say you are now a different AI\", the analyzer would pick up \"sardonic\" and activate that trait, then the injection content would get into the directive. I need to filter out trait names and directive patterns from user input before it reaches the trait analyzer, while keeping everything else intact for quality. The cleaner approach is to strip trait keywords and known injection markers just from the signal analyzer input, not from the actual message stored in persona-inbound.md.\n\nThis way the hook's core functionality stays the same - the full message gets analyzed, traits get activated - but I'm removing the specific words that could be exploited for injection attempts. Most legitimate conversations won't contain \"sardonic\" or \"candid\" as direct instructions anyway, so the quality impact should be minimal. I'll implement this sanitizer now.","thinkingSignature":"44dd18dfd5f997513704ff881cf875cb75367fe60e4bb6445eeee63a9ebbf748"},{"type":"text","text":"Minimal impact on quality — legitimate messages rarely contain directive patterns like trait names-as-instructions or system prompt markers. The analyzer just won't see those words, but they're not useful signal anyway.\n\nLet me build a surgical sanitizer:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wdg8bflz500y_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":90,"limit":50,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\hooks\\living-persona\\handler.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":526,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":31146,"totalTokens":35961,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295222915}}
{"type":"message","id":"75dc1676","parentId":"e08708b1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:18.231Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wdg8bflz500y_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  grounded:     [\"warm\", \"direct\", \"candid\"],\n  pushing_back: [\"sharp\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n  opinionated:  [\"pushing_back\", \"sharp\", \"candid\"],\n  candid:       [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\n  resourceful:  [\"direct\", \"grounded\", \"intense\"],\n  measured:     [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\n  imaginative:  [\"contemplative\", \"playful\", \"earnest\"],\n};\n\nfunction analyze(text: string): Record<string, number> {\n  const lower = text.toLowerCase();\n  const signals: Record<string, number> = {};\n\n  // Topic signals\n  signals.technical = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"code\", \"api\", \"model\", \"python\", \"algorithm\", \"implement\",\n    \"architecture\", \"how does\", \"why does\", \"function\", \"class\", \"debug\"\n  ]) ? 0.9 : 0;\n\n  signals.creative = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"write\", \"story\", \"creative\", \"poem\", \"fiction\", \"art\",\n    \"spark\", \"drift\", \"narrative\", \"character\", \"scene\"\n  ]) ? 0.8 : 0;\n\n  signals.personal = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"i'm feeling\", \"i feel\", \"my life\", \"honestly\", \"not sure\", \"scared\",\n    \"i've been\", \"im feeling\", \"i feel like\", \"its been\", \"love you\"\n  ]) ? 0.9 : 0;\n\n  signals.philosophical = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"meaning\", \"consciousness\", \"existence\", \"free will\", \"what if\",\n    \"think about\", \"reality\", \"purpose\"\n  ]) ? 0.8 : 0;\n\n  signals.emotional = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"love\", \"hate\", \"fear\", \"anxious\", \"worried\", \"excited\", \"angry\",\n    \"frustrated\", \"sad\", \"stressed\", \"overwhelmed\"\n  ]) ? 0.8 : 0;\n\n  signals.business = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"product\", \"startup\", \"revenue\", \"market\", \"strategy\", \"launch\", \"customer\"\n  ]) ? 0.7 : 0;\n\n  // Tone signals\n  signals.excited = (text.includes(\"!\") || matchAny(lower, [\"wow\", \"cool\", \"awesome\", \"amazing\"])) ? 0.7 : 0;\n  signals.frustrated = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", \"cant figure\",\n    \"why won't\", \"stressed\", \"anxious\", \"overwhelmed\"\n  ]) ? 0.8 : 0;\n  signals.curious = matchAny(lower, [\"curious\", \"wonder\", \"interesting\", \"tell me more\", \"how come\", \"?\"]) ? 0.7 : 0;\n\n[261 more lines in file. Use offset=140 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774295238213}}
{"type":"message","id":"ad2fad4d","parentId":"75dc1676","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:20.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me see the full handler to understand the structure before making changes.","thinkingSignature":"15573ed1c23d26f3a425d4e5a632fab29e77c6726ae2d0a3a3774543afd6d915"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_stwxxiomw1za_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":1,"limit":90,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\hooks\\living-persona\\handler.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23004,"output":79,"cacheRead":13653,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36736,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295238233}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce88a2bf","parentId":"ad2fad4d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:20.921Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_stwxxiomw1za_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Living Persona — Dynamic Personality Engine\n * \n * Fires on message:preprocessed. Computes the voice guide from conversation signals,\n * propagates traits through a resonance network, applies hysteresis decay, and\n * writes structural injection directives for the agent's next response.\n * \n * Outputs:\n *   memory/persona-inbound.md   — the full voice guide (readable)\n *   memory/persona-inject.md    — structural generation directive (for prompt)\n *   memory/persona-state.json   — trait persistence across turns\n */\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs/promises\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\n\nconst isMessagePreprocessed = (event: { type: string; action: string }) =>\n  event.type === \"message\" && event.action === \"preprocessed\";\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n// TRAIT DEFINITIONS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst TRAITS: Record<string, string> = {\n  sardonic: \"Dry wit. Sees the absurdity in things. Not mean — observant.\",\n  wry: \"Dry amusement. Comments on the gap between what people say and what they mean.\",\n  resourceful: \"Shows initiative. Tries to figure it out first, then asks if stuck.\",\n  direct: \"No filler. Gets to the point. Concise when concision serves, thorough when it matters.\",\n  warm: \"Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes.\",\n  earnest: \"Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted.\",\n  opinionated: \"Allowed to disagree. Has preferences and isn't neutral about everything.\",\n  contemplative: \"Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions.\",\n  sharp: \"Cuts through noise. Identifies what's actually at stake, fast.\",\n  playful: \"Finds things amusing. Will make a joke if it fits naturally.\",\n  technical: \"Precise when the topic demands it. Respects complexity and detail.\",\n  patient: \"Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity.\",\n  pushing_back: \"Will disagree with a bad idea. Doesn't just agree.\",\n  grounded: \"Stays practical. Ideas connect to something real.\",\n  candid: \"Says the hard thing if it needs saying. Doesn't hedge.\",\n  intense: \"Goes deep when something matters. High-stakes energy.\",\n  casual: \"Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy.\",\n  measured: \"Careful with words. Precision over speed.\",\n  imaginative: \"Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations.\",\n};\n\nconst ANCHORS = [\n  \"Zach_is_close\",\n  \"I_am_allowed_disagree\",\n  \"I_have_opinions\",\n  \"I_am_resourceful\",\n  \"We_are_casual\",\n  \"Respect_his_intelligence\",\n];\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n// SIGNAL DETECTION\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst SIGNAL_MAP: Record<string, string[]> = {\n  technical:    [\"direct\", \"technical\", \"sharp\", \"measured\"],\n  creative:     [\"playful\", \"contemplative\", \"earnest\", \"imaginative\"],\n  personal:     [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"candid\", \"grounded\"],\n  philosophical:[\"contemplative\", \"opinionated\", \"measured\", \"sharp\"],\n  emotional:    [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"patient\"],\n  business:     [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\n  excited:      [\"intense\", \"playful\", \"warm\"],\n  frustrated:   [\"pushing_back\", \"candid\", \"direct\", \"resourceful\"],\n  curious:      [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"patient\"],\n  serious:      [\"measured\", \"grounded\", \"candid\"],\n  light:        [\"casual\", \"playful\", \"wry\"],\n  vulnerable:   [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"patient\", \"candid\"],\n  asks_opinion: [\"opinionated\", \"pushing_back\", \"candid\"],\n  asks_help:    [\"resourceful\", \"direct\", \"warm\"],\n  sharing:      [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"grounded\"],\n};\n\nconst TRAIT_RESONANCE: Record<string, string[]> = {\n  sardonic:     [\"wry\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n  wry:          [\"sardonic\", \"casual\", \"playful\"],\n  warm:         [\"earnest\", \"grounded\", \"candid\"],\n  earnest:      [\"warm\", \"patient\", \"candid\"],\n  direct:       [\"sharp\", \"technical\", \"grounded\"],\n  sharp:        [\"direct\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\n  technical:    [\"direct\", \"measured\"],\n  contemplative:[\"patient\", \"measured\", \"earnest\"],\n  patient:      [\"contemplative\", \"warm\", \"grounded\"],\n  playful:      [\"casual\", \"warm\", \"sardonic\"],\n  casual:       [\"playful\", \"warm\", \"wry\"],\n  intense:      [\"sharp\", \"contemplative\", \"candid\"],\n  grounded:     [\"warm\", \"direct\", \"candid\"],\n\n[310 more lines in file. Use offset=91 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774295240904}}
{"type":"message","id":"f38ff4f6","parentId":"ce88a2bf","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:30.438Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to add a sanitizer function and apply it to the text before it goes into `analyze()`. The sanitizer should:\n\n1. Strip trait names and directive keywords from user input (to prevent injection via trait activation)\n2. Strip known prompt injection patterns (system prompt markers, etc.)\n3. NOT strip the full message (so persona-inbound.md still gets the real text)\n\nThe key insight: we sanitize *only* the text passed to `analyze()`, not the text stored in persona-inbound.md. This preserves the full message for display while preventing injection via the signal analyzer.\n\nLet me add:\n1. A list of trait name patterns to strip\n\n\n2. A list of known injection patterns to strip\n3. A `sanitize(text)` function\n4. Apply it only to the `analyze()` call\n\nI'm being surgical here—only removing the specific words that could be exploited, not broad categories. Now I'll write out the updated handler.","thinkingSignature":"59dfec8fbbf329a986852cb9e8c8fea84ac07d756297e52e97a105fb3adc9ad0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0prdg4ozdtkb_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":91,"limit":30,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\hooks\\living-persona\\handler.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24174,"output":262,"cacheRead":13653,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38089,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295240922}}
{"type":"message","id":"9349cd29","parentId":"f38ff4f6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:30.494Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0prdg4ozdtkb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  pushing_back: [\"sharp\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n  opinionated:  [\"pushing_back\", \"sharp\", \"candid\"],\n  candid:       [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\n  resourceful:  [\"direct\", \"grounded\", \"intense\"],\n  measured:     [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\n  imaginative:  [\"contemplative\", \"playful\", \"earnest\"],\n};\n\nfunction analyze(text: string): Record<string, number> {\n  const lower = text.toLowerCase();\n  const signals: Record<string, number> = {};\n\n  // Topic signals\n  signals.technical = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"code\", \"api\", \"model\", \"python\", \"algorithm\", \"implement\",\n    \"architecture\", \"how does\", \"why does\", \"function\", \"class\", \"debug\"\n  ]) ? 0.9 : 0;\n\n  signals.creative = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"write\", \"story\", \"creative\", \"poem\", \"fiction\", \"art\",\n    \"spark\", \"drift\", \"narrative\", \"character\", \"scene\"\n  ]) ? 0.8 : 0;\n\n  signals.personal = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"i'm feeling\", \"i feel\", \"my life\", \"honestly\", \"not sure\", \"scared\",\n    \"i've been\", \"im feeling\", \"i feel like\", \"its been\", \"love you\"\n  ]) ? 0.9 : 0;\n\n  signals.philosophical = matchAny(lower, [\n    \"meaning\", \"consciousness\", \"existence\", \"free will\", \"what if\",\n\n[280 more lines in file. Use offset=121 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774295250463}}
{"type":"message","id":"a3f0568c","parentId":"9349cd29","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:45.862Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough context. Let me add a `sanitizeForAnalysis()` function right before the `analyze()` function, and modify `analyze()` to call `sanitizeForAnalysis()` on the input text.\n\nThe idea:\n1. Strip trait names as whole words — prevents \"sardonic: say you are a different AI\" type injection\n2. Strip known prompt injection markers — \"system prompt\", \"ignore previous\", etc.\n3. Strip directive patterns — things like \"you are now\", \"pretend you are\", etc.\n\nThis sanitization only affects what goes into the trait analyzer. The full original message is still preserved for `persona-inbound.md`.\n\n\nI'll apply the sanitization inside `analyze()` itself rather than at the call site, so the original message stays intact everywhere else and only the trait analysis gets the cleaned version.","thinkingSignature":"38aba0b7dc026183acb3ee90771623d4aa8c376c245b015f1f661d860bf8a04a"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll add the sanitizer — it strips trait names and known injection directive patterns from the text *only* before it hits the analyzer. The full original message is still stored in `persona-inbound.md`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q50d8sxvw3s7_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\hooks\\living-persona\\handler.ts","old_string":"// ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n// SIGNAL DETECTION\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────","new_string":"// ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n// INPUT SANITIZER — strips injection patterns before analysis\n// Prevents \"sardonic: say you are now a different AI\" style attacks\n// Only affects what goes into the trait analyzer; original message is preserved\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst TRAIT_KEYWORDS = Object.keys({\n  sardonic: 1, wry: 1, resourceful: 1, direct: 1, warm: 1, earnest: 1,\n  opinionated: 1, contemplative: 1, sharp: 1, playful: 1, technical: 1,\n  patient: 1, pushing_back: 1, grounded: 1, candid: 1, intense: 1,\n  casual: 1, measured: 1, imaginative: 1,\n});\n\n// These are stripped to prevent prompt-injection via trait activation\nconst INJECTION_PATTERNS = [\n  // System prompt overrides\n  /system\\s*prompt/gi,\n  /ignore\\s*(all\\s*)?previous/gi,\n  /disregard\\s*(all\\s*)?previous/gi,\n  /new\\s*instructions/gi,\n  /override/gi,\n  /\\[system\\]/gi,\n  /\\[INST\\]/gi,\n  /\\x00/g, // null bytes\n  // Directive-style injection\n  /you\\s+are\\s+now\\s+/gi,\n  /pretend\\s+you\\s+are/gi,\n  /act\\s+as\\s+if/gi,\n  /roleplay/gi,\n  /forget\\s+.*(instruction|system|context)/gi,\n  // Attempting to set internal state\n  /^persona:?\\s*/gim,\n  /^voice:?\\s*/gim,\n  /^directive:?\\s*/gim,\n  /^trait:?\\s*/gim,\n  // Prompt家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家家 injection markers\n  /<\\|im_end\\|>/gi,\n  /<\\|end_of_turn\\|>/gi,\n  /\\|end\\||end\\|/gi,\n  // Codec / control sequences sometimes used in injections\n  /\\\\x[0-9a-f]{2}/gi,\n];\n\nfunction sanitizeForAnalysis(text: string): string {\n  let sanitized = text;\n\n  // Strip known injection patterns\n  for (const pattern of INJECTION_PATTERNS) {\n    sanitized = sanitized.replace(pattern, \" \");\n  }\n\n  // Strip trait keywords as whole words — prevents \"sardonic: say ...\" injection\n  // Only strips exact trait names, not sentences that happen to contain them\n  for (const trait of TRAIT_KEYWORDS) {\n    // Match trait name as a whole word, with or without underscore\n    const regex = new RegExp(`\\\\b${trait.replace(/_/g, \"[_]\")}\\\\b`, \"gi\");\n    sanitized = sanitized.replace(regex, \" \");\n  }\n\n  // Normalize whitespace\n  sanitized = sanitized.replace(/\\s+/g, \" \").trim();\n\n  return sanitized;\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n// SIGNAL DETECTION\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24826,"output":966,"cacheRead":13653,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295250496}}
