{"type":"message","id":"7ff53851","parentId":"39dbfcba","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:33:29.282Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `ollama search` command doesn't exist in this version. Let me try `ollama list` to see what's available locally and check the Ollama library online for what models are available.\n\nActually, I should just pull the model directly. The model mentioned in the holds was `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` but that's a full model name that includes the GGUf format. On Ollama, you'd use it as `hauhuacs/qwen3.5-35b-a3b-uncensored:hauhaucs-aggressive` or similar.\n\nLet me try to pull a good uncensored model. The most well-known powerful uncensored models on Ollama include:\n\n\n- `qwen2.5-72b-instruct-q4_0` (large but very capable)\n- `llama3.3-70b-instruct` \n- Various uncensored variants\n\nFor Zach's use case, the Qwen 3.5 35B or 72B would be ideal given his RTX 5000 with 30GB VRAM. The `qwen2.5-72b-instruct-q4_0` should fit in around 40GB with proper quantization, so let me attempt pulling that first.\n\nActually, given the 30GB VRAM constraint, I'll go with the 35B model instead since it can run in about 20GB with Q4_0 quantization. I'm going to try pulling `qwen2.5-72b-instruct-q4_k_m` or `qwen2.5-35b-instruct-q4_K_M` and see if Ollama has it available. I should also check the Ollama library directly to confirm what's actually accessible.","thinkingSignature":"87608f10b4b5913bb7b0ce0aae52d699baaca1786c706f2271347a0d9da94e6d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mem35etnc5ew_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s https://ollama.ai/library/qwen2.5/models 2>&1 | Select-String -Pattern '\"name\"|\"size\"|'\"'\"'quant'\"'\"'\" | Select-Object -First 30","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mem35etnc5ew_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\dev -Recurse -Include \"*.ipynb\" | Select-Object FullName","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall"