{"type":"message","id":"9e1e3fd6","parentId":"314c7ee4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:34:24.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! Now I can see the Ollama library models. The available models include:\n\nFor uncensored high-quality models that would fit in ~30GB VRAM:\n- `qwen3.5:397b` - too large (397B params, 397GB)\n- `qwen3-next:80b` - 80B, ~48GB quantized - might be too large\n- `qwen3-vl:235b` - 235B - too large\n\nBut the key question is: what uncensored models are available? The standard Qwen models from Ollama library are generally aligned/filtered. For uncensored, we'd need:\n\n\n1. Models from Ollama library that are known to be less filtered\n2. Or custom GGUF files\n\nLooking at what's actually available and uncensored: there's `devstral-small-2:24b` at 51.6GB which is too large, and various others that are either too big or aligned. The real constraint here is Zach's 30GB VRAM on his RTX 5000 - `qwen2.5-72b` in Q4_K_M would compress down to roughly 40GB, which barely fits.\n\nThe 35B models are more realistic: `qwen2.5-35b` at Q4_0 would be around 20GB, and there's `nemotron-3-nano:30b` which is actually a solid choice at 32.6GB. The problem is identifying which of these models are actually uncensored. From what I can recall, Ollama's official library models like `qwen2.5-72b` or `qwen2.5-35b` tend to have safety training applied, so I'd need to look for community models or GGUF files specifically flagged as uncensored to get something that bypasses those restrictions.\n\nGiven Zach's setup with 30GB VRAM and the HOLD2 notes pointing to `Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`, I should check if that specific community variant exists on Ollama. For the VRAM constraint, `qwen2.5-35b-instruct-q4_K_M` would fit comfortably at around 20GB, though I need to find an uncensored version of that model. The `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` model is available on HuggingFace but I'd need to convert it to GGUF format for Ollama to use it. Given the 30GB VRAM constraint, the `qwen2.5-35b` model at Q4 quantization (roughly 20GB) would be the better choice if uncensored variants are available. Now I'm trying to find all the notebooks scattered across Zach's system.\n\nI'm locating notebooks in the dev folder—there's one at the root level and another in the temporal-attention project—plus a few others I've already identified like the SRMoE training notebook. Once I have the complete list, I'll set up a notebooks directory in the dev folder and start pulling the best uncensored model that fits the VRAM requirements.","thinkingSignature":"a832c0c726ff2c40749f13067a0f6d200a4e80ffe3040c0daa8158651f47e88f"},{"type":"text","text":"Good data. Let me get the full notebook list and pull a strong uncensored model in parallel:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ffzdch2nxstz_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"fast-river","timeout":10000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ffzdch2nxstz_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\dev -Recurse -Include \"*.ipynb\" 2>$null | ForEach-Object { $_.FullName }","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ffzdch2nxstz_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects -Recurse -Include \"*.ipynb\" 2>$null | ForEach-Object { $_.FullName }","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ffzdch2nxstz_4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if HauhauCS Qwen exists on Ollama library\ncurl -s \"https://ollama.ai/api/tags?name=qwen3.5-35b\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30728,"output":934,"cacheRead":13653,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45315,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774305241831}}
