{"type":"message","id":"461062e0","parentId":"7c988d1d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:35:28.993Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see only qwen2.5 isn't in the list of models from that query. The Ollama library uses different naming conventions. Let me try to pull a known model. \n\nLooking at what we have:\n- `qwen3-next:80b` — 80B, Q4 would be ~48GB. Too large for 30GB VRAM\n- `qwen3.5:397b` — 397B, way too large\n\nLet me try `ollama show qwen2.5:35b` or just `ollama pull qwen2.5:35b` to see what happens.\n\nActually, looking at the model list - the standard Ollama naming convention is just `qwen2.5:35b` or `qwen2.5:72b`. Let me try those without the `-instruct` suffix or with other quantization.\n\n\nI think the issue is that Ollama uses camelCase naming like `qwen2.5-72b-instruct-q4_K_M`, but the API is returning different formats. Let me just attempt to pull `qwen2.5:35b` directly and see if Ollama can resolve it - if the specific quantization isn't available, it should either download the default or tell me what's actually available.","thinkingSignature":"412c878a03385b55b45a0da8a57ac747f0e91774f526243fa511694e6c6c7e61"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iso7xrt6j9lk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try the standard model names\nollama show qwen2.5:35b 2>&1","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iso7xrt6j9lk_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Also try pulling the qwen3 next which is the latest and has 80B\n# 80B Q4 = ~48GB, might still be too large\n# Let's also check what specific Qwen models are available\ncurl -s \"https://registry.ollama.ai/v2/library/qwen2.5/tags\" 2>&1 | Select-String -Pattern \"35b|72b|70b\" | Select-Object -First 20","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34843,"output":449,"cacheRead":13653,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48945,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"tot