{"type":"message","id":"e0b14440","parentId":"b1614785","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:06:30.592Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"AppData\\Local\\Programs has:\n- PhpStorm: 2.78GB\n- Ollama: 2.40GB\n- Python: 1.79GB\n- Microsoft VS Code: 0.93GB\n- cursor: 0.76GB\n- ComfyUI: 0.69GB\n\nNow the big mystery is: the disk shows 475GB used, but we've only identified ~70GB across all these locations. Let me check if there's a paging file or hibernate file taking space. Also check if the user's Downloads folder has large files, or if there are other drives with data.","thinkingSignature":"247d5532059749ef0c6968c5025cd8cf5ea339bb721f651de990ec8a9e9e7720"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fvnar1024468_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check pagefile, hibernate, other system files\n$pf = Get-ItemProperty \"HKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\Memory Management\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nWrite-Host \"PagingFiles: $($pf.PagingFiles)\"\n$hib = Get-ItemProperty \"HKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Power\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nWrite-Host \"HibernateFileSize: $($hib.HibernateFileSize)\"\n# Check if there's a D: or other drives\nGet-PSDrive | Select-Object Name, @{N='FreeGB';E={[math]::Round($_.Free/1GB,1)}}, @{N='UsedGB';E={[math]::Round($_.Used/1GB,1)}} | Format-Table -AutoSize","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106177,"output":330,"cacheRead":13653,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120160,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307181408}}
