{"type":"message","id":"43bb9c30","parentId":"7622ee29","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:09:03.171Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I don't have elevated permissions. Let me check for OneDrive files that might be占用 space, or check for a large Recycle Bin.\n\nActually, let me focus on the practical issue: we have 30GB free. With 30GB free, I can download `qwen2.5:14b` (about 9GB Q4) or `qwen2.5:32b` (about 19GB Q4). Either would be a massive upgrade over the 3B models. \n\nActually, let me check what's the best model we can fit in 30GB. Let me look up the sizes:\n- qwen2.5:14b Q4_K_M = ~8.5GB\n\n\n- qwen2.5:32b Q4_K_M = ~18.5GB\n- qwen2.5:72b Q4_K_M = ~47GB\n\nThe 32B could work with 18.5GB, though 14B is the safer choice if I want room to breathe. Though \"top of the line uncensored\" suggests going bigger—ideally 72B, but that needs 47GB and we only have 30GB free. Let me see if I can free up more space by clearing the Windows Subsystem for Android or other installed apps.","thinkingSignature":"9a091c671d41b3b25875af91511bb3354be6953ab4e62591d0dd0d6b48bd3358"},{"type":"text","text":"30GB free now. Let me try pulling a model that fits — `qwen2.5:14b` (~8.5GB) while we figure out where the other ~240GB went:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e5riad2bnbde_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ollama pull qwen2.5:14b 2>&1","yieldMs":8000,"background":true,"timeout":600}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e5riad2bnbde_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what's in DRIVER folder - could be GPU drivers taking space\nGet-ChildItem C:\\DRIVER -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object Length -Sum | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"DRIVER: $([math]::Round($_.Sum/1GB,2)) GB\" }\n# Check if there's a WSL taking space\nif(Test-Path C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Packages) {\n    Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Packages -Directory | Where-Object { $_.Name -like \"*Ubuntu*\" -or $_.Name -like \"*WSL*\" -or $_.Name -like \"*Docker*\" } | ForEach-Object {\n        $size = (Get-ChildItem $_.FullName -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object Length -Sum).Sum\n        Write-Host \"$($_.Name): $([math]::Round($size/1GB,2)) GB\"\n    }\n}\n# Check recycle bin\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\`$Recycle.Bin\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object Length -Sum | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"Recycle.Bin: $([math]::Round($_.Sum/1GB,2)) GB\" }","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109600,"output":682,"cacheRead":13653,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123935,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307327663}}
